intro: Schiedeella confusa, commonly known as the narrow-leafed mistletoe, is a hemiparasitic plant native to Australia. It belongs to the family Viscaraceae and is characterized by its evergreen leaves and small, white, fleshy fruits. The plant attaches itself to the branches of host trees, such as eucalyptus, and derives some of its nutrients from the host. Its flowers are typically greenish-white and are pollinated by insects. Schiedeella confusa plays a role in local ecosystems by providing food for birds and insects.
